@c extended commands

@c Include an image in a variety of ways: 1/ The Info format includes
@c unchanged.  2/ XHTML first tries SVG then PNG in the ``raster''
@c subdirectory; if both fail, we leave a textual tombstone.  Here,
@c the CSS must take care of centering of the graphic.  3/ TeX and
@c PDFTeX center the graphic.
@macro vimage{filename}
@ifinfo
@image{\filename\}
@end ifinfo
@html
<object data="\filename\.svg" type="image/svg+xml" width="100%" height="100%">
  <param name="src" value="\filename\.svg" />
  <object data="raster/\filename\.png" type="image/png">
    <param name="src" value="raster/\filename\.png" />
    <p>[Image "<samp><span class="file">\filename\</span></samp>" is
not displayed, because of lacking <acronym>SVG</acronym> and
<acronym>PNG</acronym> support.]</p>
  </object>
</object>
@end html
@iftex
@center@image{\filename\}
@end iftex
@end macro


